<p># ⭐ **DAY 4**</p>
<p>## **Character &ndash; Empathy &amp; Relationships**</p>
<p>**Active listening**</p>
<p>Spend 10 minutes listening to someone without interrupting.</p>
<p>If alone, recall a past conversation and imagine listening fully.</p>
<p>**Kind action**</p>
<p>Do one small act of kindness (compliment, help, support).</p>
<p>**Perspective exercise**</p>
<p>Pick one problem and write how the other person might be feeling.</p>
<p>**Reflection**</p>
<p>Write how you made someone feel understood or supported.</p>
<p>---</p>
<p>## **Speaking &ndash; Speed &amp; Pacing**</p>
<p>**Slow drill**</p>
<p>Read a paragraph slowly, focusing on clarity.</p>
<p>**Speed variation**</p>
<p>Alternate between slow and normal speed while reading.</p>
<p>**Pause training**</p>
<p>Pause naturally at commas and periods.</p>
<p>**Reflection**</p>
<p>Note moments where you rushed or slowed too much.</p>
<p>---</p>
<p>## **English &amp; Urdu &ndash; Accent &amp; Tone**</p>
